INSERT INTO `v4_wp_posts` VALUES (309, 2, '2008-09-28 00:32:33', '2008-09-27 22:32:33', 'Here you\'ll find some info about the master\'s program SEDS ((Software engineering of Distributed Systems)) in ICT ((Information and Communciation Technologie)) at KTH ((Kungliska Tekniska Högskulan)) in Stockholm, Schweden.\r\n\r\n<h2>Erlang</h2>\r\n<h3>Magic Cookie</h3>\r\nIf you have ever wondered, why you can communicate to another node of your own domain\'s system without manually setting a magic cookie ((The <i>magic cookie</i> in Erlang is kind of a authentification string send over to other nodes with every message beeing send. So the receiving system can check wether to accept the message or not. How this is done in detail can be read at <a href="http://www.erlang-fr.org/erlang.org/doc/getting_started/getting_started.html#security">Erlang Security</a>.)) as an argument <code>-setcookie</code>, the answer is as followed:\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First, the node creates a random atom as its magic cookie, but all other nodes assume the atom <code>nocookie</code> for all other nodes.</li>\r\n	<li>After the <i>auth server</i> did start (so for this case without the <code>-setcookie</code> flag), it reads a file named <code>$HOME/.erlang.cookie</code>. If the file <code>$HOME/.erlang.cookie</code> does not exist, it is created with a random string as its content. You can check and verify this your own current cookie with the command <pre lang="erlang">erlang:get_cookie()</pre> ((You can lookup information about things like this module function at <a href="http://www.erlang.org/doc/man/auth.html">Auth Module</a>)).</li>\r\n	<li>Then the function <pre lang="erlang">erlang:set_cookie(node(), CookieAtom)</pre> sets the magic cookie.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\nThat means, using <pre lang="erlang">erlang:set_cookie(node(), nocookie).</pre> makes a node completely acceptable to any received message from any node.', 'SEDS (Software Engineering of Distributed Systems)', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '219-revision-8', '', '', '2008-09-28 00:32:33', '2008-09-27 22:32:33', '', 219, 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=309', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
