e this article, my build number was <code>74</code>.)). If it can not find that, it will download or update a version from the Wula.la server <code>update1.wual.la</code>, <code>update2.wual.la</code>, <code>update3.wual.la</code>, etc. If it can find it, it will launch this application. This application which seems to be a jar container is roughly <strong>12MB</strong> big. In this container, you find all kind of Java libraries and resources. But the core application seems to be at <code>~/Library/Application Support/Wuala/Program2/Wuala.BUILDNUMBER/com/wuala</code>(<code>/application</code>). What I found a bit suspicious was the use of the <a href="http://www.divshare.com/integrate/api">DivShare API library</a> ((<a href="http://www.divshare.com/">DivShare</a> is an online storage where you can upload and download files for a certain amount of subscription fee.)), because if you decompile the class files you will find a line of code saying <pre lang="java">HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection)(new URL("http://upload.divshare.com/api/upload/")).openConnection();</pre>. I could not proof if they use this service to upload the 1GB redundant data there or if it is just a typical service they have implemented like facebook and skype including all their API library.\n\nBy the way: I\'m no hacker at all and I really appreciate the work of the wua.la team since I\'m very interested in their work and that kind of science area. And I would like to support their work wherever I can (I have no problems with advertisments). But as I was diving through the code I found a funny line of code in <code>/com/wuala/facade/dialog/preferences/advanced/AdvertisementPropertiesFacade.java</code>saying: <pre lang="java">boolean canToggleAds = user.isPro() || user.getModificationDate() < 0x9c1e2a00L;</pre> ((<em>0x9c1e2a00L</em> is hex for <em>2619222528</em> aka. Friday, November 24th 1916, 19:20:32 (GMT).)) ;-)</pre>', 'Wuala - A distributed filesystem concept', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '347-autosave', '', '', '2008-11-13 11:09:01', '2008-11-13 09:09:01', '', 347, 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=359', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
