INSERT INTO `v4_wp_posts` VALUES (362, 2, '2008-09-28 01:32:59', '2008-09-27 23:32:59', 'Here you\'ll find some info about the master\'s program SEDS ((Software engineering of Distributed Systems)) in ICT ((Information and Communciation Technologie)) at KTH ((Kungliska Tekniska Högskulan)) in Stockholm, Schweden.\r\n\r\n<h2>Erlang</h2>\r\n<h3>Magic Cookie</h3>\r\nIf you have ever wondered, why you can communicate to another node of your own domain\'s system without manually setting a magic cookie ((The <i>magic cookie</i> in Erlang is kind of a authentification string send over to other nodes with every message beeing send. So the receiving system can check wether to accept the message or not. How this is done in detail can be read at <a href="http://www.erlang-fr.org/erlang.org/doc/getting_started/getting_started.html#security">Erlang Security</a>.)) as an argument <code>-setcookie</code>, the answer is as followed:\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First, the node creates a random atom as its magic cookie, but all other nodes assume the atom <code>nocookie</code> for all other nodes.</li>\r\n	<li>After the <i>auth server</i> did start (so for this case without the <code>-setcookie</code> flag), it reads a file named <code>$HOME/.erlang.cookie</code>. If the file <code>$HOME/.erlang.cookie</code> does not exist, it is created with a random string as its content. You can check and verify this your own current cookie with the command <pre lang="erlang">erlang:get_cookie().</pre> ((You can lookup information about things like this module function at <a href="http://www.erlang.org/doc/man/auth.html">Auth Module</a>)).</li>\r\n	<li>Then the function <pre lang="erlang">erlang:set_cookie(node(), CookieAtom).</pre> sets the magic cookie.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\nThat means, using <pre lang="erlang">erlang:set_cookie(node(), nocookie).</pre> makes a node completely acceptable to any received message from any node.', 'SEDS (Software Engineering of Distributed Systems)', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '219-revision-9', '', '', '2008-09-28 01:32:59', '2008-09-27 23:32:59', '', 219, 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=362', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `v4_wp_posts` VALUES (363, 2, '2008-11-17 01:14:15', '2008-11-16 23:14:15', '<a rel="lightbox" href="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/rise-against-and-city-and-colour.png"><img src="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/rise-against-and-city-and-colour-100x100.png" alt="" title="Rise Against &#038; City and Colour" width="100" height="100" class="reflex itiltnone alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-364" /></a>Rise against has released a new album <a href="http://www.myspace.com/riseagainst">Rise against - Appeal to reason</a> some days ago (maybe months now ;-)) and I really like it. But when having study stress for the exams the funniest (insider) joke was a certain lyric line in the track <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aWTXfvfjRYo">Audience of one</a> going like this:<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Identities assume us \r\nAs nine and five add up\r\nSynchronizing watches \r\nTo the seconds that we lost</blockquote>\r\n\r\nMy recommendations of most lovings:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Kotov Syndrome</strong><br />I don\'t get it. This had to be the official opener first track! It just creates pressure! And then those long holding hymns. "Awesome!" ;-) and a nice guitar solo.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Savior</strong><br />I love the opening! And then the rest: business as usual - it just rocks! Straight forward in your face. And a little bit of anger ;-)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Hairline Fracture</strong><br />Strange beginning, takes some time and sounds a bit like <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KiR838VOCrA">Paramore\'s Misery Business</a> (she has such a nice voice in this acoustic version). But the refrain is great. Very catchy tune.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>From Heads University</strong><br />Best chorus voices from them ever! :-)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\nAnother good tip as I think of is the newest but maybe not so new <a href="http://www.cityandcolour.ca/">City and Colour</a> album <a href="http://www.myspace.com/dallasgreen">Bring me your love</a>. The lead guitarist from the scremo band <a href="http://www.theonlybandever.com/">Alexisonfire</a> who sounds quite similar to <a href="http://www.kristoferastrom.com/">Kristofer Åstrom</a> (who I really like!) was back in the beginning of this year. Same style as ever but just great. Melancholic winter guitar music with lots of emotion and "realness" ;-) I haven\'t heard all songs long enough to have good recommendations, but I really like <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CVwijXeLwLA">this</a> one song. I\'m a bit sad that I missed him on his tour in Germany this spring. Maybe next time in 2009 in Sweden hopefully.', 'Music tip: Rise against & City and Colour', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'music-tip-rise-against-city-and-colour', '', '', '2008-11-17 01:26:24', '2008-11-16 23:26:24', '', 0, 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=363', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
