INSERT INTO `v4_wp_posts` VALUES (378, 2, '2008-11-27 11:24:16', '2008-11-27 09:24:16', '<img src="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/portmap-icon.png" alt="" title="Port Map App Icon" width="128" height="128" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-380" />Port Map is an Mac OS X application for setting port mappings on your router. To make you understand what Port Map can do for you, here are some quotes from the <a href="http://www.codingmonkeys.de/">developers</a>: \r\n<blockquote>Some times you want to access your computers at home from anywhere in the world. Be it the web server on your home server, the file sharing on your desktop machine or a remote login to your parent\'s computer to support them doing their work. <!--more-->\r\n\r\nThis is where the application "Port Map" might come handy. Originally written as a proof of concept for our framework, it\'s a fully featured all-purpose port mapper supporting all major routers, with presets and URL templates.</blockquote>.\r\n\r\nThe cocoa application is open-source (MIT License) to use software and is based on their own developed framework <a href="http://code.google.com/p/tcmportmapper/">TCMPortMapper</a> which is available for further implementation and usage for developers. This framework makes use of the nice <a href="http://miniupnp.free.fr/">MiniUPnP library</a> by Thomas Bernard. You can find code samples and a usage description at <a href="http://code.google.com/p/tcmportmapper/wiki/BasicUsage">google code</a>. \r\n\r\n<div class="download">You can download Port Map <a href="http://www.codingmonkeys.de/portmap/download">here</a> v1.1</div>\r\n\r\nBelow you\'ll see a screenshot from the app with a clean and nice interface (and some iPhone UI elements ;-) maybe they will really swap over to the desktop OSes) \r\n\r\n<a rel="lightbox" href="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/portmap-screenshot.png"><img src="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/portmap-screenshot-100x100.png" alt="" title="PortMap Screenshot" width="100" height="100" class="itiltnone reflex alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-379" /></a>', 'Port Map', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'port-map', '', '', '2008-12-06 23:16:52', '2008-12-06 21:16:52', '', 0, 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=378', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
