INSERT INTO `v4_wp_posts` VALUES (383, 2, '2008-12-14 15:29:43', '2008-12-14 13:29:43', '<img src="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/natsulion-icon-100x100.png" alt="NatsuLion App Icon" title="NatsuLion App Icon" width="100" height="100" class="reflex itiltnone alignright size-small wp-image-390" />Since many of my friends seemt to have a Twitter break I went up on the horse again but this time searching for a nice and OS X integrated Twitter client. I used to have <a href="http://iconfactory.com/software/twitterrific">Twitterific</a> in my Dock, but since my Windows times I don\'t like any application that thinks it needs a theme to look cool. Cool for me is working in an evironment where all apps follow the same <a href="http://developer.apple.com/ue/">user interface style</a>, as Apple recommends. But for Mac there were not many alternatives. Either you use Twitterific with ads (or, OK, pay for it) or use my Terminal <a href="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=107">PHP Twitter Script</a> (but without any autonotification) or one of these Adobe Air ((Adobe Air lets you bundles Flash SWF "apps" into OS independant applications, which at the moment are still lacking in performance and integration.)) apps (<a href="http://twhirl.org/">Twhirl</a>, <a href="http://www.tweet-r.com/">Tweetr</a>) or - new for me - one of these Titanium ((<a href="http://titaniumapp.com/">Appcelerator\'s Titanium</a> tries to do the same as Adobe Air and Sliverlight but open-source on base of javascript, html, ...)) apps (<a href="http://titaniumapp.com/demos">Tweetanium</a>). But they are lacking much OS X integration (no window closing aloud, no growl usage, etc.). So I searched and searched and finally found the application <a href="http://www.natsulion.org/">NatsuLion</a>, which surprised me even more with it nice similar <a href="http://iphone.natsulion.org/">iPhone client</a>. <!--more--> Here are some features I would like to mention which made those two my best choice:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Really <strong>nice OS X user interface</strong> integration\r\nNot a single "extra" theme feature. Just fluent looking</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Freeware!</strong><strong>\r\nYou can play around with the sourcecode and don\'t have to pay anything or getting ads in your twitter stream</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Growl integration &amp; Sparkle ((Sparkle is an Cocoa Framework to manage nice and integrated update features.)) support</strong>\r\nUse Growl to have your new tweets beeing displayed in a Growl popup</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Unread Tweets</strong>\r\nA view to show only unread tweets keeps the app even less information grouded than showing you all the old tweets that you really don\'t want to see anymore.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>iPhone Client</strong></li>\r\nNot even does it have the desktop client but also a iPhone app with almost similar user interface. Besides that it also has:</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Unread</strong> feature</li>\r\n	<li>Choose between <strong>integrated or Safari web content view</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Bright or dark color theme</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Autopagerize</strong>\r\nTo first load the last 20 tweets and then - when you scroll down - fetch another 20 tweets and so on.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class="download"><a href="http://www.natsulion.org/download/NatsuLion.zip">Download Mac OS X Client</a></div>\r\n<div class="download"><a href="http://phobos.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewSoftware?id=289977677&amp;mt=8">Download iPhone Client</a></div>\r\nSure, Twitterific has the nicest icon, but for me, NatsuLion has the nicest client. (So... why not put the Twitterific icon into the NatsuLion.App folder? ;-)\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/ss_en_light.png" alt="NatsuLion app screenshot with bright theme" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/ss_en_dark.png" alt="NatsuLion app screenshot with dark theme" />', 'NatsuLion - Nicest Twitter Client around?', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'natsulion-nicest-twitter-client-around', '', 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=107\nhttp://titaniumapp.com/demos', '2008-12-15 10:39:21', '2008-12-15 08:39:21', '', 0, 'http://www.kreisquadratur.de/blog/?p=383', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
